Durban-  A 32-year-old woman was shot after she refused to hand over her valuables to two men during a robbery in Phoenix, north of Durban on Wednesday. Members of Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) arrived at the scene and found the woman being treated by paramedics from a private ambulance service for a gunshot wound to her right thigh. Spokesperson for RUSA Prem Balram alleged that the victim was on her way to her place of employment when she was accosted by two men near the railway lines. "The suspects asked the victim to hand over her valuables when she refused. One suspect then drew a firearm and shot her in the leg before he stole her cellphone from her handbag. The two men then fled the scene on foot. The injured female managed to flag down a passing motorist who loaded her into his vehicle and drove to a nearby business premises where they sought assistance,"Balram said. A search was conducted for the robbers however no arrests were made. KwaMashu police are investigating the incident. Daily News